The paper deals with the coexistence of Wi-Fi and LTE-LAA networks, which involves aspects of network infrastructure, communication theory, and network engineering. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), which deals with the design, implementation, and analysis of networked systems. The paper also involves analytical modeling, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory), and the impact of network parameters, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper deals with issues of fairness and coexistence, which fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), respectively.
